{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2013}} [[File:Big Kahuna Burger (small).png|right|thumb|A Big Kahuna Burger as seen in ''[[Pulp Fiction (film)|Pulp Fiction]]'']] '''Big Kahuna Burger''' is a fictional chain of [[Hawaii]]an-themed [[fast food]] restaurants that has appeared in films by [[Quentin Tarantino]] and [[Robert Rodriguez]], including ''[[Death Proof]]'', ''[[Four Rooms]]'', ''[[Pulp Fiction (film)|Pulp Fiction]]'', ''[[From Dusk till Dawn|From Dusk Till Dawn]]'' and ''[[Reservoir Dogs]]''.<ref>{{citation|title=Intertextuality and Intersemiosis |quote=13–15 February 2003|page=135|author=Marina Grishakova, Markku Lehtimäki|year=2004|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=K9tkAAAAMAAJ|isbn=978-9985-56-911-5}}</ref> The packaging was created by Tarantino's old friend Jerry Martinez.<ref>{{citation|title=Product Placement Takes a Little Twist|publisher=Greensboro News and Record|date=Jul 12, 1996}}</ref> The restaurant features most prominently in Tarantino's [[Pulp Fiction|''Pulp Fiction'',]] in which [[Samuel L. Jackson]]'s character Jules eats a Big Kahuna Burger and remarks, "This ''is'' a tasty burger!" There is a restaurant in Imperial Beach (San Diego), CA that claims to be the original ‘Big Kahuna Burger’ restaurant.{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}
In Pulp Fiction, the burger appears to be a typical American beef burger with cheese, lettuce, and tomato on a hamburger bun. Multiple real restaurants have featured a 'Big Kahuna Burger' on their menus, including Atomic Burger in [[Oxford]], [[England]].<ref>[http://www.mauigrille.com/content/00/01/55/99/03/userimages/Maui%20Grille%20Feb%2008.pdf Maui Grille] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090105191538/http://www.mauigrille.com/content/00/01/55/99/03/userimages/Maui%20Grille%20Feb%2008.pdf |date=5 January 2009 }}, in [[Surprise, Arizona]] with a "Big Kahuna Burger"</ref><ref>[http://www.panchoandleftys.com/TheBigKahunaBurger.html "The Big Kahuna Burger"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100104120541/http://www.panchoandleftys.com/TheBigKahunaBurger.html |date=4 January 2010 }} at Pancho and Leftys, [[Hare, Texas|Hare]] (near [[Taylor, Texas]])</ref><ref>[http://www.bigkahunaspb.com/ "World Famous Big Kahuna's"] currently in Pacific Beach, San Diego, CA. A "Big Kahuna Burger" described as ' "The Best burger in Town! Featured in the movie "Pulp Fiction"</ref><ref>[http://www.brassmonkey.dk/ "Brass Monkey Tiki Bar, Copenhagen, Denmark: kahuna burger"]</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=the big Kahuna burger|url=http://atomicburger.co.uk/menu#burgers|work=Atomic Burger menu|accessdate=2 June 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120918210914/http://atomicburger.co.uk/menu|archivedate=18 September 2012|location=Britain|quote=swiss cheese, pineapple & teriyaki sauce}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bigkahunasib.com/|title=Big Kahuna's, Imperial Beach, CA - Our Menu|website=Big Kahuna's, Imperial Beach|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-27}}</ref>
