The '''Tourism Association of Koh Samui''' is a [[tourism]] organisation on [[Ko Samui]], [[Thailand]]. Founded in 1987, it is a non-profit organisation composed of over 50 members including travel professionals, restaurants, hotels and resorts, and retail businesses. Its purpose is promoting Ko Samui as a travel destination and in advocacy on behalf of tourism interests in the region.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.phcnt.net/ |title = Tourism Association of Thailand |last = |first = |date = |website = Tourism Association of Koh Samui website |publisher = Tourism Association of Koh Samui |accessdate = 24 Jul 2013 }}</ref>
==Activities== *In 2012, the Ko Samui Tourism Association coordinated with [[Bangkok Airways]] and the [[Athletic Association of Thailand]] to promote the [[Samui Island Marathon, known as the Samui Island Marathon HRH Maha Chakri Sirindhorn Princess Cup 2012]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.thaivisa.com/forum/topic/586859-special-report-bangkok-airways-hosts-marathon-promotes-tourism-in-koh-samui/ |title = ''Special Report: Bangkok Airways hosts marathon, promotes tourism in Koh Samui'' |last = |first = |date = |website = ThaiVisaForum.com |publisher = [[National News Bureau of Thailand]] |accessdate = 25 Sep 2012 }}</ref> *Studying and forecasting tourism statistics and markets and planning marketing campaigns.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.kohsamuitravel.org/koh-samui-tourism-numbers |title = Koh Samui Tourism Numbers |last = |first = |date = |website = KohSamuiTravel.org |publisher = Koh Samui Travel website |accessdate = 24 Jul 2013 }}</ref> *taking part in promotional campaigns, such as a joint "road show" with [[Bangkok Airways]] and the [[Tourism Authority of Thailand]] (TAT) in 2012 to promote new direct air service to and from [[Kuala Lumpur]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.gayatravel.com.my/news/bangkok-airways-joins-hands-with-tat-and-tourism-association-of-koh-samui-organize-sales-road-show-to-kuala-lumpur |title = Bangkok Airways Joins Hands with TAT and Tourism Association of Koh Samui organize Sales Road Show to Kuala Lumpur |last = |first = |date = 13 May 2012 |website = GayaTravel.com |publisher = Gaya Travel Magazine (Suri Media Sdn Bhd and Chandi Media Group) |accessdate = 24 Jul 2013 }}</ref> *joining with other organizations to oppose oil drilling in the Gulf of Thailand, which will endanger Ko Samui's tourism industry and market appeal.<ref> {{cite web |url = http://www.horizonhomes-samui.com/th/thailand/koh-samui-rallys-against-offshore-oil-drilling.html |title = Koh Samui Rallys Against Offshore Oil Drilling |last = |first = |date = |website = HorizonHomes-Samui.com website |publisher = Horizon Homes Real Estate Company |accessdate = 24 Jul 2013 }}</ref> The association is a supporter of the [[Rak Aao Thai Network Group]], an alliance formed to fight the oil drilling. Other groups supporting the network include the Spa Association of Koh Samui, t Koh Samui Municipality, [[Suratthani Rajabhat University]], the [[Thai Hotel Association]]'s local region, and the Surat Thani Trade and Commerce Association, and various environmental and conservation groups.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://issuu.com/discoversamui/docs/06_august_2010 |title = Protestors Across Samui Rally Against Offshore Oil Drilling |last = |first = |date = |work= Samui Gazette |accessdate = 6 Aug 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://thailandtimes.asia/thailand-news/kill-the-drill-koh-samui-drilling-protest/ |title = Kill the Drill: Koh Samui drilling protest |last = |first = |date = 27 Jul 2010 |website = thailandtime.asia |publisher = Thailand Times webzine |accessdate = 24 Jul 2013 }}</ref>
